  "texts": [
    "For instance, not masking a direct identifier, such as a person's full name, is more harmful than not masking a quasi-identifier, e.g., a date.",
    "Moreover, direct identification is avoided only if all occurrences of direct identifiers are masked, not just some.",
    "With this in mind, and inspired by the work of Pilán et al. (2022), two additional LRbased metrics are proposed: the Levenshtein Recall for Direct Identifiers (LRDI) and the Levenshtein Recall for Quasi-identifiers (LRQI).",
    "Consider a list of length l di that contains the direct identifiers from ON.",
    "Let S di be the list of LSIs measured for each direct identifier, also of length l di."
  ],
